Subject: Re: [T2] how to get flywheel off?

On Wed, Jun 04, 2003 at 12:07:45PM -0700, Cha Moon wrote:
> Can someone say what i can use to take the flywheel off besides the tool specified in the bently manual?
> 
> have to keep it from spining...
> maybe i am just so worn out that i am overlooking something ..

that tool is available at most VWFLAPS ,but you can also use a piece
of bar stock. say 1" x 3/16" x 36". drill 2 holes in it so that it
will align up w/ 2 of the clutch mounting bolt holes. use this bar to
"hold" the flywheel while loosening the mounting bolts. good luck.

